COLOMBO - Bangladesh captain Mashrafe Mortaza won the toss and chose to bat in the first of a two-match Twenty20 series against Sri Lanka on Tuesday.Bangladesh handed a debut to pace bowling all-rounder Mohammad Saifuddin for the match at Colombo's R. Premadasa Stadium.READ: Pakistan now fourth on T20 rankings, SA in third placeSri Lanka picked Lasith Malinga and Vikum Sanjaya, who had played no part in the preceding Test and one-day international series.Sri Lanka: Kusal Perera, Dilshan Munaweera, Upul Tharanga (Capt), Chamara Kapugedera, Asela Gunaratne, Milinda Siriwardana, Thisara Perera, Seekkuge Prasanna, Nuwan Kulasekara, Lasith Malinga, Vikum SanjayaREAD: T20 cricket league puts Hong Kong on the mapBangladesh: Mashrafe Mortaza (Capt), Tamim Iqbal, Soumya Sarkar, Sabbir Rahman, Mushfiqur Rahim, Shakib Al Hasan, Mahmudullah Riyad, Mosaddek Hossain, Mohammad Saifuddin, Taskin Ahmed, Mustafizur RahmanUmpires: Ranmore Martinesz (SRI) and Raveendra Wimalasiri (SRI)AFP